00052 /* IPC traffic between swigps and swiril_gps uses a packet format
00053  * consisting of a fixed-size message header and a variable length
00054  * message body. The header contains 2 2-byte fields, a type and a
00055  * length. The variable length part depends on the type field.
00056  *
00057  *       +-------------------------------------------------+
00058  *      2| type: One of swigpsMsgType                      |
00059  *       +-------------------------------------------------+
00060  *      2| result: (Inbound only) QMI result of the request|
00061  *       +-------------------------------------------------+
00062  *      2| length: size (bytes) of variable portion (0..n) |
00063  *       +-------------------------------------------------+
00064  *       |                                                 |
00065  *      n| type-specific content                           |
00066  *       |                                                 |
00067  *       +-------------------------------------------------+
00068  */
00069 #define SWIGPS_MSGSIZE_HEADER 6
00070 #define MAXURL 128
00071 
00072 /* MIN URL is the smallest possible URL
00073  * that makes sense - in this case of
00074  * the form x.com. Very unlikely, but
00075  * possible. 
00076  */
00077 #define MINURL 5
